<===> comments.liquid
{% assign verb = "turned" %}
{% comment %}
{% assign verb = "converted" %}
{% endcomment %}
Anything you put between {% comment %} and {% endcomment %} tags
is {{ verb }} into a comment.

{% assign i = 0 %}

Putting in `-%}` here because Liquid will strip the whitespace by default while Liquex will not.

{% comment %}{{ i }}{% endcomment %}
{% for i in (1..5) -%}
  {% comment %}{{ i }}{% endcomment %}
{%- endfor %}

{% comment %}{{ i }}{% endcomment %}

### Inline Comments

{% # inline comment %}

{{ # inline comment }}

{% # for i in (1..3) -%}
  {{ i }}
{% # endfor %}

{%
  ###############################
  # This is a comment
  # across multiple lines
  ###############################
%}

{% liquid
  # this is a comment
  assign topic = 'Learning about comments!'
  echo topic
%}
